features: SAFER INGREDIENTS, POWERFUL CLEAN: Made with only 10 earth-derived ingredients, this natural formula harnesses the power of plant-based surfactants and naturally-occuring enzymes to deeply penetrate fibers, removing soil, dirt, oil, and stains with ease.

EXTRA GENTLE FOR SENSITIVE SKIN: Scented with natural peppermint oil, hypoallergenic and 100% free from harsh synthetic fragrances, dyes, and other harmful additives. Gentle, clean-rinsing detergent ideal for those with eczema or other skin sensitivities.

ULTRA CONCENTRATED FORMULA: Ultra concentrated and stain fighting, provides a powerful plant-based clean and helps conserve water. Compatible with all washers including high-efficiency (HE) machines. Septic safe, works well in hard water to break through mineral build-up and remove grey streaks and other set-in stains.

FOR MOTHERS EVERYWHERE: From Mother Earth to our family to your family. Made in the USA with simple ingredients that are vegan and certified cruelty-free by Leaping Bunny. Residue-free and clean rinsing, septic and grey water safe. Lightly scented with peppermint oil so clothes smell fresh, naturally. Safe for all mothers, babies, people, skin sensitivities, and planet for cleaning power with compassion.

WHAT'S INCLUDED: One 52 oz bottle of Liquid Laundry Detergent with easy and convenient measuring cap. Our eco-friendly, sustainable detergent is capable of deep cleaning 100 loads of laundry. Fill cap 1/2 way to first line for small loads and all the way to first line for regular or heavily-soiled loads and run on your preferred wash cycle.

Are Molly's Suds products safe for sensitive skin? Yes! Many of our customers have sensitive skin or eczema and that is why they use all of our products. There are no harsh or leaching chemicals and each product is clean rinsing. Are your detergents HE-friendly? Yes! All of our detergents are safe for standard, HE, and commercial washing machines. Our powder detergents do best when you add it directly to your drum and then toss in your laundry. Are your detergents septic-safe? Are they grey water safe? All of our laundry and cleaning products are septic-safe. Our Original Laundry Powder is grey water-safe, we even had it soil tested! Are Molly's Suds products safe to use while pregnant and/or for my baby's clothing? All of our products are safe to use during pregnancy. Our laundry products are all safe for use on baby clothing. Many parents choose our unscented laundry products for newborns, however our scented options are safe to use.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 6, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I have searched for a good clean laundry detergent for about a year that doesn’t have harsh chemicals or doesn’t irritate the skin and this one is the best so far! It smells great and cleans my clothes very well. I have tried making my own and it just leaves a weird film on my clothes. This does great with my son’s sensitive skin and doesn’t make him itchy or get a rash. I get the largest size and will last me awhile. It is definitely more on the expensive side, but it’s worth it to have a clean and safe detergent. Stop looking and buy this one.

reviews.reviewText: I am very smell sensitive and typically do not like scented anything, but I did end up getting the lavender laundry soap, both the powdered and the liquid versions and it does not bother me. It smells good but not overwhelming. It does a great job cleaning clothes and my son who was constantly itching his skin is no longer itching after his clothes have been washed with this. Also, my clothes feel a little softer.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 28, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I used half the bottle already doing a week worth of laundry but then realized I was using too much! The instructions say to use just under half the 40ml mark for a regular load and the full 40ml for a larger load. I just assumed the full cap was 40ml, which is what MOST laundry detergent packaging would be. But that’s not the case with this cap - there’s a barely visible line a little more than halfway up the cap marking the 40ml. Paying more than $20 for a small bottle like this, the packaging should be more clear or at least label the 40ml in some way that’s more clearly seen. I wasted a lot of product because of a poor packaging decision. I would suggest either a cap that is actually 40ml so there’s no confusion or at least a darker line that’s visible without searching for it. Do you even see the line in my picture of the cap? I promise it’s there - tou just can’t see it without searching. Doing my laundry shouldn’t be so complicated and not at this price. Maybe I’ll do what an other reviewer did and draw my own line. I would expect to do that off a dollar store brand but not something this expensive. You can afford better caps at this price. Other than that, the peppermint scent isn’t my favorite. It’s minty but not like the peppermint you’d expect. It’s like stale rather than bright and minty. I’m going to try the either lavender or citrus next time. This isn’t the mint type of scent I like. My clothes did smell clean when they came out though and the product does clean them without leaving any residue.
